FT  10 JUN 94 / International Company News: French groups join global
satellite telephone system
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The French telecommunications groups Alcatel Alsthom and France Telecom will
join Globalstar, a global satellite-based mobile telephone system formed by
US groups Loral and Qualcomm, AP-DJ reports from Paris.
Loral said France Telecom would own a 51 per cent interest in a joint
venture with Alcatel, which will hold 49 per cent. Total investment in the
joint venture, called Tesam, is Dollars 37.5m, and represents about 8.3 per
cent of the ownership of Globalstar. Tesam will be an owner and service
provider of Globalstar in France and 'a number of other territories', Loral
said.
Loral said Globalstar would begin service in 1998, and is expected to have
revenues of Dollars 1.6bn and 2.7m subscribers by the year 2002.
