<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 94 / International Company News: Reynolds Metals in joint deal to
build Saudi plant
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Reynolds Metals, the world's third-largest producer of aluminium cans, is to
build an aluminium beverage can plant in Dammam, Saudi Arabia, in a joint
venture with four local partners.
The plant, which is scheduled to be completed in early 1996, will have an
annual capacity of 1.2bn cans.
It will supply cans for Coca-Cola, and other soft drink brands and juices
produced by the project's Saudi shareholders.
Reynolds will provide technology for the project and manage and operate the
facility, which is expected to employ 260 people.
Reynolds' partners in the venture, in which it holds a 27.5 per cent stake,
are the Olayan Group, which owns the Coca-Cola Bottling company of Saudi
Arabia; the Olayan Financing Company; and two local soft drink and juice
producers.
