<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 94 / Arab group pays Westland Pounds 115m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Arab Organisation for Industrialisation has paid a further Pounds 115m
to Westland Helicopters, taking the legal tussle between the manufacturer
and several Arab governments a step forward.
The case followed the collapse of an Egyptian-based helicopter manufacturing
project in 1979. The organisation was set up by Saudi Arabia, Qatar, United
Arab Emirates and Egypt to make Lynx helicopters under licence. A year ago
the Geneva-based Arbitral Tribunal, which deals with international disputes,
put the damages owed to Westland at Pounds 385m. A payment of Pounds 25m was
made in February.
