<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 94 / North-south divide still shrinking
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN WILLMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Rising unemployment, falling house prices and shrinking investment have
further closed the north-south divide, the 1994 edition of Regional Trends
shows today, writes John Willman. 'Last year we said the recession was a
great leveller,' said Mrs Jenny Church, editor of the annual digest of
statistics on the UK's 11 regions. 'In 1993, the erosion of regional
differences continued - with the south-east, south-west and East Anglia hit
hardest.'
